<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Rayne on 04-27-2001 12:25 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I still have a month before my hosting at Gameglow expires, but I thought it would be a good time to explore my options.

Here's what I see:

1) Stay with Everyone.net and accept POPUP banner ads (like you get at EZBoard and other places).

2) Move to Flashlink like EQ Maps.  That means Pay per View.

3) Find some other host like Mr Fixitonline.  Let me say now though that I'm very skeptical of any site that offers me free/minimal hosting charges.  I expect that situation to get a lot worse before (if) it gets better.

4) Move back to my personal domain and pay for the bandwidth overruns out of pocket (was averaging $100 a month when I moved).  And I can pass the hat around like Sunmoon.  **Click PayPal to give Rayne ur phat ca$h**

5) Admit that running this site is almost strictly a vanity issue for me, give up the ghost, find someone to take the messages and assimilate into another site (like Caster's Realm or possibly Interrealm/Sunmoon).

6) Really give up the ghost, say "cya" and let people find an EZ Board or start dumping on some other site and cause THEM bandwidth issues =P.

So, what do people think?  I have preferences, but my mind is open.  I'm just watching the clock tick and would like to save the message boards if possible.

Rayne</TEXTAREA>
